Members of the National Coalition Group ( NCG) were in Ilorin, Kwara State on Wednesday to seek the support of the Emir of Ilorin, Alh Ibrahim Sulu-Gambari for the presidential ambition of Vice- President Yemi Osinbajo. The leader of the group, Dr Eli Dibia requested the Emir to help canvass for the emergence of someone who will be president for all Nigerians come 2023. ” We are in Ilorin to Seek the Emir’s support for Osinbajo. Emir should help canvas for a president that will be for all Nigerians, who will build on legacies of President Buhari,” headded. 2023: Coalition Vows To Mobilise 5 Million  Supporters For… 2023: Only PDP Has Pedigree To Rescue Nigeria From Insecurity,… Dibia insisted that Osinbajo remains the best presidential candidate that the All Progressives Congress (APC) can field for the 3023 presidential elections. Warning the APC leadership against fielding a wrong candidate for the elections, Dibia posited that:”The only person that the opposition is afraid of is Osinbajo. If we make the mistake of not fielding the appropriate candidate, APC may lose to the opposition. Eulogising Osinbajo’s leadership qualities, the team leader pointed out that the vice president drafted the legal framework for the development of Lagos. “He ( Osinbajo) understands the economy. He has the capacity to serve Nigerians. He’s a loyal VP. We want a servant president,” he added Responding, the Emir of Ilorin, Alh Ibrahim Sulu-Gambari prayed God to grant the country a peaceful transition in 2023. POLL While acknowledging the federal government’s efforts at curtailing various security challenges confronting the country, the monarch prayed for the restoration of peace to all the nooks and crannies of the country. He thanked the pro- Osinbajo presidency team for the visit and wish them well in their programmes.